  <releases>
    <release version="2.0.2" type="stable" date="2026-6-4">
      <description>
        <p>QPrompt 2.0.2 is a bug fix release.</p>
        <p>The following issues were fixedd in this release:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Fix restoration of active focus to the teleprompter</li>
          <li>Fixed opacity slider's text input field not accepting inputs correctly</li>
          <li>Fixed the tool separator for the undo-redo row not being visible at all the times when it should be visible, including upon first startup</li>
          <li>Fixed text being incorrectly selected after clicking on a marker from the list of markers (this was a regression present only in QPrompt 2.0.1)</li>
          <li>Fixed un-setting of named markers not working</li>
          <li>Fixed anchor names disappearing after loading anchors from a saved document</li>
          <li>Removed a non-working context-menu button to show the font dialog appearing in platforms where system font selection isn't possible</li>
          <li>Prevented automatic but invisible auto-selection of markers when clicking on them</li>
          <li>Fixed regression in `no-screens` patch that caused focus not to be given to the prompter when starting the prompter via the mouse.</li>
          <li>Fixed play button state inconsistencies</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
      <url>https://github.com/Cuperino/QPrompt-Teleprompter/releases/tag/v2.0.2</url>
      <artifacts>
        <artifact type="source">
          <location>https://github.com/Cuperino/QPrompt/archive/refs/tags/v2.0.2.tar.gz</location>
        </artifact>
      </artifacts>
    </release>
    <release version="2.0.1" type="stable" date="2026-3-28">
      <description>
        <p>QPrompt 2.0.1 is a bug fix release.</p>
        <p>The following issues were fixed in this release:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Improved Chinese translation</li>
          <li>Fixed font selector popup showing up behind Pointer Settings</li>
          <li>Removed unused icons</li>
          <li>Improved compatibility with current versions of KDE's Kirigami framework and ExtraCMakeModules</li>
          <li>Fixed contextual page actions not showing on context drawer on mobile Linux distros</li>
          <li>Fixed Appdata metadata</li>
          <li>Fixed errors with markers list that would lead to undefined behavior and assertions on debug builds</li>
          <li>Fixed error with handle bars that would lead to an assertion on debug build for iOS</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
      <url>https://github.com/Cuperino/QPrompt-Teleprompter/releases/tag/v2.0.1</url>
      <artifacts>
        <artifact type="source">
          <location>https://github.com/Cuperino/QPrompt/archive/refs/tags/v2.0.1.tar.gz</location>
          <checksum type="sha256">e7ceed01f02cbeb531e97299239ea4b3f332f8b7685cbb3c383329c2dff668a2</checksum>
        </artifact>
      </artifacts>
    </release>
    <release version="2.0.0" type="stable" date="2026-1-1">
      <description>
        <p>QPrompt 2.0.0 is a major release. It brings about many features and bug fixes and completes our transition to using version 6 of the Qt and KDE framework.</p>
        <p>New features:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Support for many office formats by importing through LibreOffice</li>
          <li>Configure and add your own custom pointers</li>
          <li>Input text in superscript and subscript</li>
          <li>Input exact number settings via the keyboard</li>
          <li>Reset factory settings</li>
          <li>Fix a preferred language</li>
          <li>Fix the UI layout direction to RTL or LTR</li>
          <li>The settings that improve performance can now all be accessed from a single location</li>
          <li>Button to make window stay on top of other windows</li>
          <li>Find and replace</li>
          <li>Search text using expressions</li>
          <li>Ability to open remote documents</li>
          <li>Toggable auto-refresh for local documents</li>
          <li>Toggable auto-refresh for remote documents</li>
          <li>Introduced support for Apple Silicon</li>
          <li>Experimental WebAssembly build allows running from the web browser</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Improvements:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Expanded usable prompter area</li>
          <li>Improved application stability, confirmed bugs reduced to single digit numbers</li>
          <li>Improved dark mode integration on Windows</li>
          <li>Improved usability in small screens</li>
          <li>Improved UI contrast for reduced beam-split mirror glare</li>
          <li>Improved and expanded translations to many languages</li>
          <li>Improved touch controls</li>
          <li>Improved keyboard input customization experience</li>
          <li>Improved prompter smoothness (except while using screen projections)</li>
          <li>Improved UI layout and organization</li>
          <li>Improved Wayland support</li>
          <li>Expanded Unicode support</li>
          <li>Modernized application build and distribution process</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
      <url>https://github.com/Cuperino/QPrompt-Teleprompter/releases/tag/v2.0.0</url>
